results.lead_paragraph: CAPE KENNEDY, Fla., Feb. 25 (UPI) Fred W. Haise, a civilian astronaut assigned to the Apollo 13 moon flight, said today that he and Capt. James E. Lovell of the Navy planned to explore a hilly region of the moon, collect valuable subsurface samples, and possibly climb a mound 250 to 400 feet high.
